<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Apache on wlsc</title><link>https://wlsc.de/tags/apache/</link><description>Recent content in Apache on wlsc</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Mon, 13 Jun 2016 16:31:42 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://wlsc.de/tags/apache/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Apache htaccess: Force Domain HTTPS/SSL protocol</title><link>https://wlsc.de/2016/06/13/apache-htaccess-force-domain-httpsssl-protocol/</link><pubDate>Mon, 13 Jun 2016 16:31:42 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://wlsc.de/2016/06/13/apache-htaccess-force-domain-httpsssl-protocol/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;In order to redirect all users from the unsecure HTTP to the &lt;strong&gt;secure HTTPS&lt;/strong&gt; connection, you need to edit your *
&lt;em&gt;.htaccess&lt;/em&gt;* file. Usually, it is located in the root of your project (e.g., &lt;strong&gt;httpdocs&lt;/strong&gt; folder).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-apache" data-lang="apache"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;IfModule&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;mod_rewrite.c&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;RewriteEngine &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;On&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;RewriteCond %{HTTPS} !=on
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;RewriteRule ^(.*)$ https://%{HTTP_HOST}/$1 [R=301,L]
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;/IfModule&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description></item><item><title>Short URL in your GWT project</title><link>https://wlsc.de/2016/04/21/short-url-in-your-gwt-project/</link><pubDate>Thu, 21 Apr 2016 16:10:17 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://wlsc.de/2016/04/21/short-url-in-your-gwt-project/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;If you are struggling with a long URL in the GWT project, you are at the right place! There is a small trick, which
allows URL to be shorter.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="url-transformation"&gt;
 URL Transformation
 &lt;a class="heading-link" href="#url-transformation"&gt;
 &lt;i class="fa-solid fa-link" aria-hidden="true" title="Link to heading"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
 &lt;span class="sr-only"&gt;Link to heading&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;From:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0"&gt;&lt;code&gt;https://domain.com/tomcat_context_path/project_name/your_index.html
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0"&gt;&lt;code&gt;https://domain.com/tomcat_context_path/
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>